abstract: The 49ers defeated the Vikings, 27-10, in dominating fashion, including two rushing touchdowns and by capitalizing on Vikings mistakes.
lead_paragraph: SANTA CLARA, Calif. — The greats came back on Saturday, flooding a frothing Levi’s Stadium to watch their treasured San Francisco 49ers engage in a pastime foreign to their fan base for so long: playoff football. Joe Montana, Jerry Rice, Bryant Young — they all showed up, flocking to witness the latest stage of the 49ers’ revival, six years in the making.
